org.melior.cloud.config

Class CsxConfigDataLoader

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.melior.cloud.config.CsxConfigDataLoader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.springframework.boot.context.config.ConfigDataLoader<CsxConfigDataResource>, org.springframework.core.Ordered

    public class CsxConfigDataLoader
extends Object
implements org.springframework.boot.context.config.ConfigDataLoader<CsxConfigDataResource>, org.springframework.core.Ordered
    An extension to the client side of the Spring Cloud Config Server. This class loads ConfigData for a given CsxConfigDataResource. The ConfigData injects a PropertySource with config properties that have the following effects:
    • The host name is presented in a host.name config property.
    • The user may set the spring.cloud.config.profile or spring.cloud.config.label config property to ${host.name} to send the host name to the Spring Cloud Config Server as either the profile or the label.
    • If no profile is active and the user has not set the spring.cloud.config.profile config property, then the spring.cloud.config.profile config property is automatically set to ${host.name}.
    • If one or more profiles are active, but the user prefers to send some other value to the Spring Cloud Config Server as the profile, then the user may set an environment.name config property or an ENVIRONMENT_NAME environment variable as an alternative to setting the spring.cloud.config.profile config property.
    Since:
    2.3
    Author:
    Melior
    See Also:
    CsxConfigDataLocationResolver, CsxConfigDataResource
